<h1>CSS Styling of Namespaces in HTML</h1>
</div>
<p class="warning" style="color: red">Prerequisite: <strong>STOP! Your browser doesn't support embedded CSS; this test is meaningless.</strong></p>

<p>Control: <span class="test">This text must be green, for this test to be meaningful.</span></p>

<p>Test 1: <ex1:test>If this text is green, your browser supports styling of root namespaces.</ex1:test></p>

<p>Test 2: <ex2:test xmlns:ex2="http://www.aaronsw.com/2002/HTMLnamespaces#t2">If this text is green, your browser supports styling of embedded namespaces.</ex2:test></p>

<p>Test 3: <ex3:test>If this text is red, your browser isn't looking at the namespaces at all.</ex3:test></p>

<p>Test 4: <ex4:text xmlns:ex4="http://www.aaronsw.com/2002/HTMLnamespaces#t4">If this text is green, your browser supports @namespace properly on embedded namespaces.</ex4:text></p>

<h2>Test Results</h2>
<p><strong>Key:</strong> <strong>G</strong>reen, <strong>B</strong>lack, <strong>R</strong>ed.</p>

